Privacy Policy
Effective Date: 7/01/2025
Last Updated: 7/01/2025
Thank you for using Kids Web Filter extension. Your privacy is important to us, and we are committed to protecting it. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your information when you use our Chrome extension.

1. Information We Collect
We may collect the following information when you use the extension:

URLs of websites you visit (if required for the extension’s functionality).
Metadata or content associated with specific web pages (e.g., titles, tags, or media files).
User preferences and settings related to the extension.
We do not collect personal information such as your name, email address, or other identifiable details unless explicitly required and consented to by you.

2. How We Use Your Information
We use the information collected to:

Provide the features and functionality of the extension.
Improve performance, fix bugs, and enhance user experience.
We do not sell or share your information with third parties, except as necessary for the operation of the extension or as required by law.

3. Warning About Privacy Risks
By installing and using Kids Web Filter extension, you acknowledge and agree to the following:

The extension may access and process data related to your browsing activity, depending on its functionality.
While we strive to ensure the security of your data, we cannot guarantee absolute protection against unauthorized access or misuse.
By installing this extension, you accept that there may be privacy risks associated with its usage.
If you do not agree to these terms, please do not install or use this extension.

4. Data Security
We use industry-standard practices to secure your information. However, no method of electronic storage or transmission over the internet is 100% secure. Use the extension at your discretion.

5. Your Rights
You have the right to:

Access, modify, or delete any personal data stored by the extension, where applicable.
Uninstall the extension if you no longer agree to this privacy policy.
6. Changes to This Policy
We reserve the right to update this Privacy Policy at any time. Changes will be posted on this page, with the "Last Updated" date modified accordingly.

7. Contact Us
If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:
liewjoee@gmail.com


Acknowledgment
By installing and using Kids Web Filter extension, you acknowledge that you have read, understood, and agreed to this Privacy Policy.
